Stevo writ:



> unsure that might be too hot.  meantime, the bed of my DC has a
> side-to-side seam never apparently welded, but leaks and allows a lake in
> the cargo/rear cab. would i be wrong in having this seam welded, or use a
> more flexible filler since it wasn't welded at the factory?

They're all like that. I used a flowable silicone windshield sealant to fill
it, stopped the leakage and it flows into the crack so it can't be seen. Be
sure to do it AFTER you have painted.

